The US foundation banned from operating in Kenya and its Sh2 billion account frozen has been working in this country since 2002, it has emerged.The International Foundation for Electoral Systems originally assisted the now-defunct Electoral Commission of Kenya with electoral review processes.In 2010, IFES provided technical support to the IIEC on the implementation of an electronic results transmission system and later provided support to the IEBC. It helped in voter registration, results transmission, oversight of political parties and civic education.On Monday, NGO Coordination Board executive director Fazul Mohamed suspended IFES activities, saying the organisation is operating in Kenya illegally.On Sunday, National Assembly majority leader Aden Duale accused IFES head Michael Yard of helping Cord leader Raila Odinga to rig the 2017 polls.Yard is a recognised international election administration and technology expert with over 25 years experience.